net.sf.jclec.mo.command

Class PopulationSplitter

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.command.Command
      • net.sf.jclec.mo.command.PopulationSplitter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC

    public class PopulationSplitter
extends Command
    This command splits the population in subsets according to a comparison criterion. Here, any comparator extending from MOIndividualsComparator can be used. The given population is not modified during the execution of the command. The resulting subsets store copies of the individuals. These sets of solutions can be retrieved after the execution of the command using a getter method that will return a list of lists.

    The subsets are created in the following way:

    1. The individuals that are better than any other individual are stored in the first set.
    2. The individuals that are better than any other individual, after discarding those belonging to the first set, are stored in the second set.
    3. The process continues until all the individuals are included in their corresponding subset.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

      • execute

        public void execute()
        Execute the command.

        This command uses a comparator to divide the population in different sets. It uses the comparator stored in comparator. The partitions will be stored in splitPopulation, so it can be then obtained using getSplitPopulation() method.
